=== READING THE SPREAD ===
  Compare each K's window std against that K's mean Δ. If std is a
  large fraction of |mean|, the gain a single K delivers is largely
  a lottery on which seeds were drawn; a small std => the gain is
  robust. K=10 should show a smaller range than K=5 if averaging
  more seeds stabilises the gain.

